# Combining Conditions

Remember the logical operators (`&&` and `||`) from Chapter 3? They are the perfect tool to prevent messy, nested `if` statements!

Instead of checking one thing, going inside, and checking another, we can combine them into a single, clean test.

### The Nested Way (Bulky):
```javascript
if (score >= 100) {
  if (lives > 0) {
    console.log("You win!");
  }
}
```

### The Logical Way (Clean!):
```javascript
if (score >= 100 && lives > 0) {
  console.log("You win!");
}
```

